sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant KRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.3
    participant vLLM as vLLM OpenAI API Server<br/>8000/TCP HTTP
    participant Runner as HPUModelRunner
    participant HPU as Intel Gaudi HPU<br/>(Gaudi2/Gaudi3)
    participant S3 as Model Storage<br/>(S3/HuggingFace/PVC)
    participant Ray as Ray Head<br/>6379/TCP
    participant Peer as HPUWorker Peers<br/>(Rank 1..N)
    participant HCCL as HCCL Peer HPUs<br/>RDMA/TCP

    Note over Client, HCCL: Flow 1: Model Inference Request

    Client->>KRBAC: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token
    KRBAC->>KRBAC: Validate token against<br/>Kubernetes API Server
    KRBAC->>vLLM: Forward (HTTP localhost)<br/>Pre-authenticated
    vLLM->>Runner: Schedule inference batch<br/>(bucketed shapes)
    Runner->>HPU: Execute compiled graph<br/>(attention + FFN)
    HPU-->>Runner: Token logits
    Runner-->>vLLM: Generated tokens
    vLLM-->>KRBAC: JSON Response
    KRBAC-->>Client: HTTPS Response<br/>TLS 1.3

    Note over Client, HCCL: Flow 2: Distributed Multi-HPU Inference

    Runner->>Ray: Register worker (Rank 0)<br/>TCP 6379
    Ray->>Peer: Initialize workers (Rank 1..N)<br/>TCP dynamic
    Runner->>HCCL: All-reduce gradients<br/>RDMA/TCP
    Peer->>HCCL: All-gather activations<br/>RDMA/TCP
    HCCL-->>Runner: Synchronized tensors
    HCCL-->>Peer: Synchronized tensors

    Note over Client, HCCL: Flow 3: Model Weight Loading (Startup)

    Runner->>S3: Download model weights<br/>HTTPS 443/TCP<br/>Auth: HF_TOKEN or AWS IAM
    S3-->>Runner: Model artifacts<br/>(safetensors/bin)
    Runner->>Runner: Apply quantization<br/>(FP8/GPTQ/AWQ/INC)
    Runner->>HPU: Transfer weights to<br/>HPU device memory
    Note right of HPU: Compile execution graphs<br/>for bucketed shapes
